cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO

This paper deals with the task of intrinsic image decomposition, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel learning approach that involves unsupervised reconstruction error, which falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the second most likely category. The paper also involves explaining the input image, which is a task that requires reasoning and understanding, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The paper also involves predicting lighting conditions, which is a task that falls under the subfield of computer graphics, making cs.GR (Graphics) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves predicting shape, which is a task that falls under the subfield of robotics, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category as well.
